### 2.3 High-Risk Area #2: Authentication & Authorization

**Why High-Risk:**

- Authentication bypass = complete system compromise
- Improper authorization = data access violations
- Session hijacking = unauthorized actions

**Risk Scenarios:**

1. **Authentication Bypass**

   - Password reset token prediction
   - JWT token forgery
   - Brute force login attempts
   - Session fixation attacks

2. **Authorization Failures**

   - Viewer role can edit/delete data
   - Quality role can approve Stage 2 qualification
   - User can escalate own privileges
   - API endpoint authorization missing

3. **Session Management**
   - Sessions don't expire
   - Logout doesn't invalidate tokens
   - Concurrent session abuse
   - Token refresh vulnerabilities

**Test Strategy:**

```
Priority: P0 (Critical)
Test Coverage: 95%+
Test Types: Unit, Integration, Security, Penetration
```

**RBAC Test Matrix:**

| Feature                       | Admin   | Procurement | Quality | Viewer  |
| ----------------------------- | ------- | ----------- | ------- | ------- |
| Create Supplier               | ✅ PASS | ✅ PASS     | ✅ PASS | ❌ FAIL |
| Delete Supplier               | ✅ PASS | ✅ PASS     | ❌ FAIL | ❌ FAIL |
| Approve Qualification Stage 2 | ✅ PASS | ✅ PASS     | ❌ FAIL | ❌ FAIL |
| Approve Qualification Stage 3 | ✅ PASS | ❌ FAIL     | ✅ PASS | ❌ FAIL |
| Close Complaint               | ✅ PASS | ❌ FAIL     | ✅ PASS | ❌ FAIL |
| View Dashboard                | ✅ PASS | ✅ PASS     | ✅ PASS | ✅ PASS |
| Export Data                   | ✅ PASS | ✅ PASS     | ✅ PASS | ❌ FAIL |
| Manage Users                  | ✅ PASS | ❌ FAIL     | ❌ FAIL | ❌ FAIL |

**Test Automation:**

```typescript
describe("Authentication & Authorization", () => {
  describe("Login", () => {
    it("should accept valid credentials", async () => {
      const response = await api.post("/auth/login", {
        email: "user@example.com",
        password: "ValidPass123!",
      });

      expect(response.status).toBe(200);
      expect(response.data.access_token).toBeDefined();
      expect(response.data.user.tenant_id).toBeDefined();
    });

    it("should reject invalid password", async () => {
      const response = await api.post("/auth/login", {
        email: "user@example.com",
        password: "WrongPassword",
      });

      expect(response.status).toBe(401);
      expect(response.data.error).toBe("invalid_credentials");
    });

    it("should lock account after 5 failed attempts", async () => {
      const email = "user@example.com";

      // Attempt 5 failed logins
      for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        await api.post("/auth/login", { email, password: "wrong" });
      }

      // 6th attempt should be locked
      const response = await api.post("/auth/login", {
        email,
        password: "ValidPass123!", // Even with correct password
      });

      expect(response.status).toBe(429);
      expect(response.data.error).toBe("account_locked");
    });
  });

  describe("RBAC - Viewer Role", () => {
    let viewerUser;

    beforeEach(async () => {
      viewerUser = await createTestUser({ role: "viewer" });
    });

    it("should allow viewing suppliers", async () => {
      const response = await api.get("/suppliers", { auth: viewerUser });
      expect(response.status).toBe(200);
    });

    it("should deny creating suppliers", async () => {
      const response = await api.post("/suppliers", {
        auth: viewerUser,
        body: { name: "Test Supplier" },
      });

      expect(response.status).toBe(403);
      expect(response.data.error).toBe("insufficient_permissions");
    });

    it("should deny exporting data", async () => {
      const response = await api.get("/suppliers/export", { auth: viewerUser });
      expect(response.status).toBe(403);
    });
  });

  describe("JWT Token", () => {
    it("should reject expired token", async () => {
      const expiredToken = generateExpiredToken();
      const response = await api.get("/suppliers", {
        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${expiredToken}` },
      });

      expect(response.status).toBe(401);
      expect(response.data.error).toBe("token_expired");
    });

    it("should reject tampered token", async () => {
      const validToken = await generateValidToken();
      const tamperedToken = validToken.slice(0, -10) + "TAMPERED";

      const response = await api.get("/suppliers", {
        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${tamperedToken}` },
      });

      expect(response.status).toBe(401);
      expect(response.data.error).toBe("invalid_token");
    });
  });
});
```

