### 2.5 High-Risk Area #4: File Upload Security

**Why High-Risk:**

- Malicious file uploads = server compromise
- Unvalidated files = XSS/malware
- Unbounded uploads = storage exhaustion
- Path traversal = file system access

**Risk Scenarios:**

1. **Malicious File Upload**

   - Executable files uploaded (.exe, .sh)
   - Script files with XSS payload
   - Malware/virus uploads
   - ZIP bombs / decompression attacks

2. **Storage Issues**

   - No size limits = storage exhaustion
   - No quota per tenant = abuse
   - Orphaned files not cleaned up
   - File overwrite attacks

3. **Access Control**
   - Files accessible without authentication
   - Cross-tenant file access
   - Direct URL guessing
   - Missing file expiration

**Test Strategy:**

```
Priority: P0 (High)
Test Coverage: 95%+
Test Types: Unit, Integration, Security, Penetration
```

**Test Automation:**

```typescript
describe("File Upload Security", () => {
  it("should accept valid file types", async () => {
    const validFiles = ["document.pdf", "cert.jpg", "report.xlsx"];

    for (const filename of validFiles) {
      const response = await uploadFile(filename);
      expect(response.status).toBe(201);
    }
  });

  it("should reject executable files", async () => {
    const maliciousFiles = ["virus.exe", "malware.sh", "script.bat"];

    for (const filename of maliciousFiles) {
      const response = await uploadFile(filename);
      expect(response.status).toBe(400);
      expect(response.data.error).toBe("invalid_file_type");
    }
  });

  it("should enforce file size limit (25MB)", async () => {
    const largeFile = generateFile(30 * 1024 * 1024); // 30MB

    const response = await api.post("/documents", {
      body: { file: largeFile },
    });

    expect(response.status).toBe(413); // Payload Too Large
    expect(response.data.error).toBe("file_too_large");
  });

  it("should sanitize file names", async () => {
    const response = await uploadFile("../../../etc/passwd"); // Path traversal

    expect(response.status).toBe(400);
    expect(response.data.error).toBe("invalid_filename");
  });

  it("should enforce tenant isolation for file access", async () => {
    const tenantA = await createTestUser({ tenant: "tenant-a" });
    const tenantB = await createTestUser({ tenant: "tenant-b" });

    // Tenant A uploads file
    const upload = await api.post("/documents", {
      auth: tenantA,
      body: { file: "secret.pdf" },
    });

    // Tenant B attempts to access
    const response = await api.get(`/documents/${upload.data.id}`, {
      auth: tenantB,
    });

    expect(response.status).toBe(404); // Not 403
  });

  it("should generate secure, unpredictable file URLs", async () => {
    const urls = [];

    for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
      const upload = await uploadFile(`file${i}.pdf`);
      urls.push(upload.data.url);
    }

    // URLs should not be sequential or predictable
    expect(new Set(urls).size).toBe(10); // All unique
    expect(urls[0]).toMatch(/^https:\/\/.*\/[a-f0-9-]{36}\//); // UUID pattern
  });

  it("should expire pre-signed URLs after 1 hour", async () => {
    const upload = await uploadFile("document.pdf");
    const url = upload.data.url;

    // Immediately accessible
    const response1 = await fetch(url);
    expect(response1.status).toBe(200);

    // After 1 hour + 1 minute (mock time)
    jest.advanceTimersByTime(61 * 60 * 1000);

    const response2 = await fetch(url);
    expect(response2.status).toBe(403); // Forbidden - expired
  });

  it("should perform virus scanning", async () => {
    // Mock virus scanner
    mockVirusScanner.mockReturnValueOnce({ infected: true, virus: "EICAR" });

    const response = await uploadFile("infected.exe");

    expect(response.status).toBe(400);
    expect(response.data.error).toBe("virus_detected");
  });
});
```

**Security Checklist:**

- [ ] File type whitelist enforced (PDF, DOC, DOCX, XLS, XLSX, JPG, PNG, GIF)
- [ ] File size limit enforced (25MB)
- [ ] Filename sanitization (remove path traversal, special chars)
- [ ] Virus scanning on upload (ClamAV or cloud service)
- [ ] Files stored with UUID names (not original names)
- [ ] Pre-signed URLs with 1-hour expiration
- [ ] Tenant isolation in storage paths
- [ ] No direct file system access (use Supabase Storage)
- [ ] File metadata stored in database with tenant_id
- [ ] Orphaned file cleanup job runs daily

