### 2.6 High-Risk Area #5: Performance & Scalability

**Why High-Risk:**

- Slow system = poor user experience = churn
- Unoptimized queries = database overload
- No caching = high costs
- Memory leaks = system crashes

**Risk Scenarios:**

1. **Database Performance**

   - Missing indexes on large tables
   - N+1 query problems
   - Inefficient joins
   - Unbounded result sets

2. **API Performance**

   - Slow response times (> 1s)
   - No pagination
   - No rate limiting
   - Memory leaks in long-running processes

3. **Frontend Performance**
   - Large bundle sizes
   - Unoptimized images
   - No lazy loading
   - Excessive re-renders

**Test Strategy:**

```
Priority: P0 (High)
Test Coverage: Key workflows
Test Types: Performance, Load, Stress, Spike
```

**Performance Benchmarks:**

| Operation                   | Target (P95) | Max (P99) | Test Data Size   |
| --------------------------- | ------------ | --------- | ---------------- |
| GET /suppliers (list)       | < 300ms      | < 500ms   | 500 suppliers    |
| GET /suppliers/{id}         | < 200ms      | < 300ms   | N/A              |
| POST /suppliers             | < 400ms      | < 600ms   | N/A              |
| GET /evaluations            | < 400ms      | < 700ms   | 200 evaluations  |
| POST /evaluations (complex) | < 600ms      | < 1000ms  | N/A              |
| GET /dashboard              | < 800ms      | < 1200ms  | Full tenant data |
| Export suppliers CSV        | < 3s         | < 5s      | 500 suppliers    |

**Test Automation:**

```typescript
describe("Performance Tests", () => {
  beforeAll(async () => {
    // Seed database with realistic data volume
    await seedDatabase({
      tenants: 10,
      suppliersPerTenant: 500,
      evaluationsPerSupplier: 4,
      complaintsPerSupplier: 2,
    });
  });

  it("should load supplier list in < 300ms (P95)", async () => {
    const measurements = [];

    for (let i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
      const start = Date.now();
      await api.get("/suppliers?per_page=25");
      const duration = Date.now() - start;
      measurements.push(duration);
    }

    const p95 = calculatePercentile(measurements, 95);
    expect(p95).toBeLessThan(300);
  });

  it("should handle pagination efficiently", async () => {
    const page1 = await api.get("/suppliers?page=1&per_page=25");
    const page10 = await api.get("/suppliers?page=10&per_page=25");

    // Last page should not be significantly slower than first
    expect(page10.duration).toBeLessThan(page1.duration * 1.5);
  });

  it("should eager-load related data to avoid N+1 queries", async () => {
    const queryCount = await getQueryCount(async () => {
      const suppliers = await api.get("/suppliers?include=category,contact");
      // Should load suppliers + categories + contacts in 3 queries total
      // NOT 1 + N queries (one per supplier)
    });

    expect(queryCount).toBeLessThanOrEqual(3);
  });

  it("should cache frequently accessed data", async () => {
    const url = "/dashboard";

    // First request (cache miss)
    const response1 = await api.get(url);
    const time1 = response1.duration;

    // Second request (cache hit)
    const response2 = await api.get(url);
    const time2 = response2.duration;

    // Cached response should be at least 2x faster
    expect(time2).toBeLessThan(time1 / 2);
  });
});

describe("Load Testing", () => {
  it("should handle 100 concurrent users", async () => {
    const results = await loadTest({
      url: "/suppliers",
      concurrentUsers: 100,
      duration: "1m",
    });

    expect(results.successRate).toBeGreaterThan(0.99); // 99%+ success
    expect(results.p95ResponseTime).toBeLessThan(500);
    expect(results.errorRate).toBeLessThan(0.01); // < 1% errors
  });

  it("should recover from traffic spike", async () => {
    // Baseline: 10 users
    await loadTest({ concurrentUsers: 10, duration: "30s" });

    // Spike: 500 users
    const spikeResults = await loadTest({
      concurrentUsers: 500,
      duration: "1m",
    });

    // System should not crash, though response times may degrade
    expect(spikeResults.successRate).toBeGreaterThan(0.95); // 95%+

    // Return to baseline: 10 users
    const recoveryResults = await loadTest({
      concurrentUsers: 10,
      duration: "30s",
    });

    // Should recover to normal performance within 30s
    expect(recoveryResults.p95ResponseTime).toBeLessThan(500);
  });
});
```

**Performance Checklist:**

- [ ] Database indexes on all foreign keys
- [ ] Database indexes on frequently queried columns (status, tenant_id, created_at)
- [ ] Pagination on all list endpoints (max 100 per page)
- [ ] Eager loading for related data (avoid N+1)
- [ ] API response caching with Redis (TTL: 5-60 minutes)
- [ ] Dashboard data cached (TTL: 5 minutes)
- [ ] Rate limiting: 1000 requests/hour per tenant
- [ ] Connection pooling configured (max 20 connections per tenant)
- [ ] Frontend code splitting by route
- [ ] Image optimization (WebP, lazy loading)
- [ ] Bundle size < 200KB gzipped

