## 3. Test Architecture

### 3.1 Test Pyramid

```
                    /\
                   /  \
                  / E2E\ (10% - Critical flows)
                 /______\
                /        \
               /  Integr. \ (30% - API + DB + Services)
              /____________\
             /              \
            /  Unit Tests     \ (60% - Business logic, utilities)
           /__________________\
```

**Distribution:**

- **Unit Tests (60%):** Fast, isolated, test business logic
- **Integration Tests (30%):** Test API + database + external services
- **E2E Tests (10%):** Test critical user flows end-to-end

### 3.2 Test Technology Stack

**Backend Testing:**

- **Framework:** Jest (Node.js) or pytest (Python)
- **Mocking:** jest-mock (built-in) or sinon
- **API Testing:** supertest (Node.js) or pytest-httpx (Python)
- **Database:** Test database instance per test suite
- **Fixtures:** Factory pattern with faker.js for test data

**Frontend Testing:**

- **Unit:** Jest + React Testing Library
- **Component:** Storybook with interaction tests
- **E2E:** Playwright (preferred) or Cypress
- **Visual Regression:** Percy or Chromatic

**Performance Testing:**

- **Load Testing:** k6 or Artillery
- **APM:** Vercel Analytics + Sentry
- **Database:** Supabase monitoring dashboard

**Security Testing:**

- **SAST:** SonarQube or Snyk
- **DAST:** OWASP ZAP
- **Dependency Scanning:** Dependabot + npm audit
- **Secret Scanning:** GitGuardian or truffleHog

### 3.3 Test Environment Strategy

```
Local Dev → CI/CD → Dev → Staging → Production

├── Local Development
│   ├── Docker Compose (PostgreSQL, Redis)
│   ├── Supabase local emulator
