## 4. Testing Strategy by Type

### 4.1 Unit Testing

**Purpose:** Test individual functions, classes, utilities in isolation

**Scope:**

- Business logic (scoring calculations, validations)
- Utility functions (date formatting, string manipulation)
- Pure functions (no I/O, no side effects)

**Coverage Target:** 80%+

**Example Test Cases:**

```typescript
// utils/scoring.test.ts
describe("calculateOverallScore", () => {
  it("should calculate weighted average correctly", () => {
    const scores = {
      quality: 4.5, // 30%
      delivery: 4.0, // 30%
      service: 4.0, // 20%
      cost: 4.3, // 20%
    };

    expect(calculateOverallScore(scores)).toBeCloseTo(4.21, 2);
  });

  it("should handle minimum scores", () => {
    const scores = { quality: 1, delivery: 1, service: 1, cost: 1 };
