## 6. Security Testing

### 6.1 Security Test Checklist

**Authentication:**

- [ ] Password requirements enforced (8+ chars, uppercase, number, special)
- [ ] Account lockout after 5 failed attempts
- [ ] Password reset tokens expire after 1 hour
- [ ] Password reset tokens are single-use
- [ ] JWT tokens expire after 8 hours
- [ ] JWT tokens cannot be forged
- [ ] Logout invalidates tokens
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials in code

**Authorization:**

- [ ] RBAC enforced on all endpoints
- [ ] Viewer cannot modify data
- [ ] Procurement cannot approve Stage 3
- [ ] Quality cannot delete suppliers
- [ ] All roles tested (see RBAC matrix)

**Input Validation:**

- [ ] SQL injection prevented (parameterized queries)
- [ ] XSS prevented (input sanitization, CSP headers)
- [ ] CSRF protection enabled
- [ ] File upload validation (type, size, content)
- [ ] Email validation
- [ ] Phone number validation
- [ ] URL validation

**Data Protection:**

- [ ] All data encrypted at rest (Supabase default)
- [ ] All data encrypted in transit (TLS 1.3)
- [ ] Sensitive fields (passwords) hashed (bcrypt)
- [ ] API keys encrypted in database
- [ ] No sensitive data in logs
- [ ] No sensitive data in error messages

**API Security:**

- [ ] Rate limiting enforced (1000/hour per tenant)
- [ ] CORS configured for specific domains
- [ ] API authentication required on all endpoints
- [ ] No verbose error messages in production
- [ ] Security headers configured (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options)

**Multi-Tenancy:**

- [ ] RLS policies on all tenant tables
- [ ] No cross-tenant data leakage
- [ ] Tenant ID from JWT, never from client
- [ ] File storage isolated per tenant
- [ ] Cache keys scoped to tenant

### 6.2 OWASP Top 10 Testing

| OWASP Risk                            | Test Strategy                                         | Priority |
| ------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | -------- |
| **A01: Broken Access Control**        | RBAC testing, multi-tenancy testing                   | P0       |
| **A02: Cryptographic Failures**       | Verify TLS, encryption at rest, password hashing      | P0       |
| **A03: Injection**                    | SQL injection, XSS, command injection tests           | P0       |
| **A04: Insecure Design**              | Security architecture review, threat modeling         | P1       |
| **A05: Security Misconfiguration**    | Security headers, default credentials, error messages | P1       |
| **A06: Vulnerable Components**        | Dependency scanning (npm audit, Snyk)                 | P0       |
| **A07: Identification/Auth Failures** | Authentication testing, session management            | P0       |
| **A08: Software/Data Integrity**      | Code signing, supply chain security                   | P2       |
| **A09: Logging/Monitoring Failures**  | Audit log testing, alerting verification              | P1       |
| **A10: Server-Side Request Forgery**  | SSRF testing (if applicable)                          | P2       |

### 6.3 Penetration Testing

**Manual Penetration Testing Scenarios:**

```
Tester: Security Team / External Auditor
Frequency: Before MVP launch, then quarterly
Scope: All MVP features
```

**Test Scenarios:**

1. **Cross-Tenant Data Access**

   - Attempt to access other tenant's data via API manipulation
   - Try URL parameter tampering
   - Test JWT token manipulation
   - Verify RLS enforcement

2. **Authentication Bypass**

   - Test weak password acceptance
   - Brute force login
   - Password reset token prediction
   - Session fixation
   - JWT forgery

3. **File Upload Exploits**

   - Upload malicious files (.exe, .sh, scripts)
   - Upload oversized files
   - Path traversal attacks
   - File type bypass (rename .exe to .pdf)

4. **Injection Attacks**

   - SQL injection in search, filters
   - XSS in text inputs
   - Command injection (if applicable)
   - LDAP injection (if applicable)

5. **Business Logic Flaws**
   - Skip qualification stages
   - Close complaint without CAPA
   - Modify finalized evaluations
   - Escalate user privileges

**Tools:**

- **OWASP ZAP** - Automated vulnerability scanner
- **Burp Suite** - Manual penetration testing
- **SQLMap** - SQL injection testing
- **Nikto** - Web server scanner

