## 7. Performance Testing

### 7.1 Performance Test Types

**1. Load Testing**

- Purpose: Verify system handles expected load
- Users: 100 concurrent users
- Duration: 1 hour
- Success: < 1% error rate, P95 response time < 500ms

**2. Stress Testing**

- Purpose: Find breaking point
- Users: Gradually increase from 100 to 1000
- Duration: Until system degrades
- Success: Identify maximum capacity, graceful degradation

**3. Spike Testing**

- Purpose: Verify recovery from traffic spike
- Users: 10 → 500 → 10 (sudden changes)
- Duration: 30 minutes
- Success: System recovers within 30 seconds

**4. Endurance Testing**

- Purpose: Find memory leaks, resource exhaustion
- Users: 50 concurrent users
- Duration: 24 hours
- Success: No performance degradation, no memory leaks

### 7.2 Performance Test Scenarios

**Scenario 1: Dashboard Load**

```
Endpoint: GET /dashboard
Concurrent Users: 100
Duration: 10 minutes
Expected RPS: 10 requests/second
Target P95: < 800ms
Target P99: < 1200ms
```

**Scenario 2: Supplier List with Filters**

```
Endpoint: GET /suppliers?status=approved&category=metal
Concurrent Users: 50
Duration: 5 minutes
Expected RPS: 20 requests/second
Target P95: < 300ms
Target P99: < 500ms
```

**Scenario 3: Create Evaluation**

```
Endpoint: POST /evaluations
Concurrent Users: 20
Duration: 5 minutes
Expected RPS: 5 requests/second
Target P95: < 600ms
Target P99: < 1000ms
```

### 7.3 Performance Testing with k6

```javascript
// tests/performance/load-test.js
import http from "k6/http";
import { check, sleep } from "k6";
import { Rate, Trend } from "k6/metrics";

const errorRate = new Rate("errors");
const dashboardTime = new Trend("dashboard_response_time");

export const options = {
  stages: [
    { duration: "2m", target: 10 }, // Ramp-up to 10 users
    { duration: "5m", target: 10 }, // Stay at 10 users
    { duration: "2m", target: 50 }, // Ramp-up to 50 users
    { duration: "5m", target: 50 }, // Stay at 50 users
    { duration: "2m", target: 100 }, // Ramp-up to 100 users
    { duration: "5m", target: 100 }, // Stay at 100 users
    { duration: "2m", target: 0 }, // Ramp-down to 0 users
  ],
  thresholds: {
    http_req_duration: ["p(95)<500", "p(99)<1000"], // 95% < 500ms, 99% < 1s
    errors: ["rate<0.01"], // Error rate < 1%
    dashboard_response_time: ["p(95)<800"],
  },
};

const BASE_URL = "https://supplex-staging.vercel.app";
const AUTH_TOKEN = __ENV.AUTH_TOKEN;

export default function () {
  // Simulate user session
  const params = {
    headers: {
      Authorization: `Bearer ${AUTH_TOKEN}`,
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
    },
  };

  // 1. Load dashboard
  let response = http.get(`${BASE_URL}/api/v1/dashboard`, params);
  check(response, {
    "dashboard status is 200": (r) => r.status === 200,
    "dashboard response time < 800ms": (r) => r.timings.duration < 800,
  });
  errorRate.add(response.status !== 200);
  dashboardTime.add(response.timings.duration);
  sleep(2);

  // 2. List suppliers
  response = http.get(`${BASE_URL}/api/v1/suppliers?per_page=25`, params);
  check(response, {
    "suppliers status is 200": (r) => r.status === 200,
    "suppliers response time < 300ms": (r) => r.timings.duration < 300,
  });
  errorRate.add(response.status !== 200);
  sleep(1);

  // 3. View supplier detail
  if (response.status === 200) {
    const suppliers = JSON.parse(response.body).data;
    if (suppliers.length > 0) {
      const supplierId = suppliers[0].id;
      response = http.get(`${BASE_URL}/api/v1/suppliers/${supplierId}`, params);
      check(response, {
        "supplier detail status is 200": (r) => r.status === 200,
        "supplier detail response time < 200ms": (r) =>
          r.timings.duration < 200,
      });
      errorRate.add(response.status !== 200);
      sleep(3);
    }
  }

  // 4. Search suppliers
  response = http.get(`${BASE_URL}/api/v1/suppliers?search=acme`, params);
  check(response, {
    "search status is 200": (r) => r.status === 200,
  });
  errorRate.add(response.status !== 200);
  sleep(1);
}

export function handleSummary(data) {
  return {
    "performance-report.html": htmlReport(data),
    stdout: textSummary(data, { indent: " ", enableColors: true }),
  };
}
```

**Run Performance Tests:**

```bash
# Install k6
brew install k6

# Run load test
k6 run tests/performance/load-test.js

# Run with environment variables
AUTH_TOKEN=xyz k6 run tests/performance/load-test.js

# Run with custom duration
k6 run --duration 10m --vus 50 tests/performance/load-test.js
```

