## 10. Quality Gates & Release Criteria

### 10.1 Quality Gates

**Gate 1: Code Commit**

- [ ] All unit tests pass
- [ ] Code coverage ≥ 80%
- [ ] Linter passes (0 errors)
- [ ] TypeScript type-check passes
- [ ] No security vulnerabilities (high/critical)

**Gate 2: Pull Request**

- [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)
- [ ] Code review approved (2+ reviewers)
- [ ] No merge conflicts
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Changelog updated

**Gate 3: Staging Deployment**

- [ ] All E2E tests pass
- [ ] Security scan passes
- [ ] Performance benchmarks met
- [ ] Manual QA approval

**Gate 4: Production Release**

- [ ] Staging validation complete
- [ ] Stakeholder sign-off
- [ ] Release notes published
- [ ] Rollback plan documented
- [ ] Monitoring alerts configured

### 10.2 MVP Release Criteria

**Functional Criteria:**

- [ ] All P0 user stories implemented and tested
- [ ] All 7 core modules functional:
  - Tenant & User Management
  - Supplier Master Data
  - Qualification Workflow (3-stage)
  - Performance Evaluation
  - Complaint Tracking & CAPA
  - Analytics & Dashboards
  - REST API
- [ ] RBAC enforced for all roles (Admin, Procurement, Quality, Viewer)
- [ ] Multi-tenancy data isolation verified (0 leaks)

**Quality Criteria:**

- [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%
- [ ] 0 P0 (critical) bugs
- [ ] ≤ 5 P1 (high) bugs
- [ ] All security tests passed
- [ ] All performance benchmarks met (P95 < 500ms)
- [ ] Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 Level A compliance

**Security Criteria:**

- [ ] 0 critical/high security vulnerabilities
- [ ] Penetration testing passed
- [ ] RLS policies tested and verified
- [ ] File upload security verified
- [ ] Authentication/authorization tested

**Performance Criteria:**

- [ ] Page load time < 2s (P95)
- [ ] API response time < 500ms (P95)
- [ ] Dashboard load time < 800ms (P95)
- [ ] System handles 100 concurrent users
- [ ] Database queries optimized (< 50ms average)

**Operational Criteria:**

- [ ] Monitoring and alerts configured
- [ ] Backup and recovery tested
- [ ] Disaster recovery plan documented
- [ ] Support documentation complete
- [ ] User guide published
- [ ] API documentation published

**Compliance Criteria:**

- [ ] GDPR compliance verified
- [ ] Data retention policies implemented
- [ ] Audit logging functional
- [ ] Terms of Service finalized
- [ ] Privacy Policy finalized

### 10.3 Bug Severity Definitions

| Severity          | Definition                                  | Response Time | Examples                                                |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| **P0 - Critical** | System down, data loss, security breach     | 1 hour        | Multi-tenancy leak, auth bypass, data corruption        |
| **P1 - High**     | Major feature broken, significant impact    | 4 hours       | Qualification workflow blocked, cannot create suppliers |
| **P2 - Medium**   | Feature partially broken, workaround exists | 1 day         | Search not working, export fails occasionally           |
| **P3 - Low**      | Minor issue, cosmetic problem               | 1 week        | UI misalignment, typos, minor performance issue         |

**Release Blocking:**

- **P0:** Always blocks release
- **P1:** Blocks release (≤ 5 allowed with documented workarounds)
- **P2:** Does not block release
- **P3:** Does not block release

